<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98675893470679></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98675893470679><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98675893470679>RE: Iksar or Human?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98675893470679#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9543><span id=Scholar>Landrion</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>31 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Apr 8th 3:42 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Iksar get higher ac, double regeneration, infravision.<br><br>Humans get a 0.1 second shorter delay for fists at level 25 and up, and they are liked by all "good" races so they can travel around Norrath easier.  Also, they have higher charisma which affects prices (75 cha to iksar's 55 cha).<br><br>The stats are different between the two also:<br><br>.......STR...STA...AGI...DEX<br>Human...80....80....85....85<br>Iksar...75....75...100....95<br><br>Both have 20 points to put where you want.<br><br>Another interesting thing is, iksar monks can wear the human monks sashes and headbands, but the iksar shackles are iksar only.<br><br>I won't express any opinion here, so you can choose just by the facts.<br><br>Zzaarno Painmaker<br>23 monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
