<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98680717880452></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98680717880452><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98680717880452>RE: newbie needs help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98680717880452#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 9th 5:06 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sell them to a Player Character (PC) instead of an Non Player Character (NPC) as you'll probably get more coin but you might have to hang onto them for a day or so. Just give a /ooc (out of character) in a couple different zones asking for what your words usually sell for then use /auction to sell them. If you started in Freeport, a good place to sell them would be East Commons(EC) and Nektulos Forest (just North of EC). If you started in Qeynos, the easiest place to sell would probably be Toxulia Forest (just take a boat and get off at the second stop, not the one with the cats). It's a little tricky at first to get around Erudin just look for teleportation pads that look like gems (and bring a fire beetle eye with you).<br><br>Note:<br>Enchanters use Pages <br>Magicians use Words, Scrolls, Shards, Other Spells and things<br>Necromancers use Words<br>Wizards use Runes<br><br>The people who use what you have are:<br>Words of Collection(Azia): Level 39 Mag Spell: Summon Mystic Dagger<br>Words of Descrying: Level 39 Necro Spell: Nullify Magic<br>Words of Requisition: Level 49 Necro Spell: Invoke Death<br><br>Unless you intend on practicing Jewelcraft (I wouldn't recommend it for a monk), just sell the Bloodstones to and amiable vendor. Ie. some one in the town you started in.<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br>Aeriform,<br>Tunare & Torv. Worlds<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
