	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a monk, I hate the change.  It makes the potion bags I was using, along with the large sewing kit, all but useless to me.  It really curtails the monk's ability to carry anything and fight.<br><br>But this is what our character is supposed to be.  Tradtionally, the monk does not care for possessions beyond the cloak on his back and maybe his walking stick.  We're not possession hungry warriors or knights.  <br><br>As a trademan (smith, brewer, tailor) I see this as a good thing.  First, those late night smithing sessions no longer get cut off becuase I mess up the FP recipe and Kaladim doesn't sell a smithy hammer.  Also, experimentation becomes feasible.  It also preserves the hand made backpack market, which has been threatened of late.  10% wt reduction might not seem like a lot, but tell that to a smith who's trying to fill her bank with folded sheets.<br><br>Also, to not add wt and make the safe combine change would make trade kits too unbalanced.  There needed to be a way to safely experiment as a tradesman, and also impose some cost on carrying the kits.<br>&nbsp;<br>Alerithon Tigerspirit<br>29 rank monk, E'Ci<br>Avatara</td></tr>
