	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I started my monk, which was about 2 years ago, there were not very many good guides on monk creation.  I created my monk with the default stats and put 10 into agility and 10 into intelligence believing that it would help with combat increases.  &lt;Sigh&gt;<br><br>Now that I'm level 34, I'm seeing monks that are lower than me do much more damage than myself and hit more often probably due to putting a lot of starting points into strength and I'm concerned that groups would have problems with me due to a lower damage output.  Does anyone know how much difference 15 to 20 points of strength makes?  I could not find a chart on this anywhere.  Currently with just my equipment I achieve anywhere between 114 to 122 strength but I have not found a really noticeable difference in comparison to others and my 1hb, hth, and 2hb are maxed.<br><br>I have a fighting baton and stormwood battle staff yet it's amazing how much less damage I have been doing in comparison with similar equipment.  My point is to ask advice from higher level monks whether they see any difference in having higher strength and from other monks to know their opinion on whether I should start over.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
