	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well all I can input is based on experience.  My human monk is 45 now, and yes I maxed our Str on creation.  So my Str with eqipment is 126.  I am often buffed to about 159 and the median range of my attacks is not that different from 126 to 159 Str.  So even if you did not max out your Str, the extra 20 points do not make a great difference in your damage output.  As far as grouping goes, I do get complaints from some clerics that my HP goes down fast (my fast damage output aggros me pretty fast especially being the puller) and they would rather have a real tank, however, my role is a group is being a great puller not a great damage taker which they luv me for.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
