<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98644460380857></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98644460380857><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98644460380857>RE: Should I Start Over?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98644460380857#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9543><span id=Scholar>Landrion</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>31 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 12:23 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The information I have for strength and damage (I forgot where I got this, sorry.) is this formula for maximum damage:<br><br>maxdamage=(weapondamage*((str+weaponskill)/100)+((level-25)/3)<br><br>So, assuming you have your weapon skill maxed (level*5)+5, at level 34, with str items bringing your str up to 122, the max damage you would do with a fighting baton (8dmg) would be 27 (26.76).<br><br>If you had put all 20 points into str and had the same str buffing items bringing your str up to 142, the max damage you would do would be 28 (28.36).<br><br>Basically what it comes down to is that for every 1 point of strength, your max damage goes up 1/100 of the weapon damage.  So, with a weapon rated at 10 dmg, for every 1 str your max damage goes up 0.1.<br><br>In my opinion, the things that affect damage the most is your level (because the weapon skill goes up 5 points every level if you max it), and the weapon.<br><br>Hope that helps 8^)<br><br>Zzaarno, level 22 iksar monk, Tholuxe-Paells server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
