<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98622429540262></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98622429540262><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98622429540262>RE: 1hb and hth at the same time?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98622429540262#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>108 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 2nd 11:11 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>YES, it is possible to raise both skills by having one in the primary and one in the secondary, HOWEVER (there's always a however, heheh) how quickly your off-hand advances depends on your dual weild skill.  So, until your DW skill gets reasonably high (I don't know, maybe 60 or so, any other figures out there) you're going to see your primary advancing a lot and your secondary barely creeping.<br><br>Solution:  alternate.  Get your 1HB up to a certain level, then switch so your club is in your left hand, rinse and repeat (a fond saying on this board I'm noticing).<br><br>2HB, that's another monster.  Unfortunately one I've put off until now.  I'm dreading the day ...<br><br>Zasshatiz - 17 Iksar Monk<br>Gluadilae - 19 Wood Elf Ranger<br>Luclin Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
