	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 2nd 5:22 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>get the lightest thing you cna get your hands on, dont bother buying anymore weapons from vendors, try and save for stuff from players. dont worry about that ac deduction for now, my monk was rarely under 15ibs until about 10-20 when i started to finally get my woven/cured armor. I do have a couple mroe tips though. <br>1) instead of buying backpacks or boxes (terribel weight) try and save for a large sewing kit or two. They have same number of slots and can hold the same size of stuff but only weigh 2ibs. <br>2) consider taking up tailoring. Keep all those pelts in the bank, and combine spider silks together when you get them. It'll really help you get a boost in your money AND if you stick with it you can make cured silk for yourself.<br>3) You CAN practice 2hb and hth at the kinda same time. The trick is make a hotkey on your main melee weapon. Put your 2hb there, and whenever you get in a tight spot, or loosing in a battle a lil just click on the hotkey to remove your 2hb so you can catch back up with your hands. This is of course assuming your hth skill is good or better than 2hb. <br><br>well i hope his helpd you and any other monks who read it =)<br><br>Please rate my posts, i like input =)<br>Nitsujlak Barshemguud Ogre Shammy<br>Blackendheart Darkendsoul Ogre Shadowknight<br>Quixotic Innerdemon Iksar Shammy<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
