	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wow, so many questions in one little post. )  Well, here's my opinion:<br><br>1)Skill points - Personally, I put one point into any new skills and horde the rest like a greedy squirrel.  My only exception was with tailoring when I got really frustrated about the skill not moving in forever.  I've heard mention of dumping extra points in Mend also, since it's such a valuable skill and relatively difficult to increase.  I can see the reasoning for that also.  Your combat skills should easily max themselves out each level just by fighting.  Keep in mind also that round kick will be replaced by Tiger Claw soon, so don't get too caught up in increasing that skill.<br><br>2)Increasing Combat Skills - Yes, it depends on how the beast cons to you.  Anything that will give you xp for killing will also possibly increase your skill.  Also, the higher the con, the more likely the increase.  Great reason for grouping those yellow cons.  This is according to other posts I've seen.<br><br>3)Cured Silk Armor - Going rate is usually 2pp per AC.  The guy I buy from will give a discount if you get the silks and/or make them into swatches for him.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Gluadilae-19 Ranger<br>Zasshatiz-14 Monk<br>Luclin Server<br><br>BTW this is my first non-anonymous post.  Please let me know what you think out there.  I've posted frequently without registering and figured I might as well make a name.  Thanks!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
