<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98632079354991></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98632079354991><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98632079354991>RE: Place to Practice Safefall</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98632079354991#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 3rd 1:59 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've done most of mine in W Freeport gate. I started running up the steps to the guard walk and running over the wall on my way out to hunt. Few hp and didn't slow me down a second.  When I stopped taking hits, I went up one level (stairs to the right) and jumped off that level (and it does scare the newbies!).  Quickly I had to jump as I went over the edge to get any hit at all. I also used the tunnel to Desert of Ro in East Commonlands.  You can run up enough to get hp but no major damage and repeat quickly.  In 2 levels I can now go above the entrance and jump w/o any hp....am now looking for higher places since I maxed those..<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
